                            <comment id="13933170" author="fmatte" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2016 10:01:54 -0700"  >From the above program it is clear that, if one is using &amp;quot;capacity + capacity&amp;gt;&amp;gt;1&amp;quot; means it is as simple as using &amp;quot;capacity&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Proper usage is &amp;quot;capacity + (capacity&amp;gt;&amp;gt;1)&amp;quot;</comment>
                            <comment id="13933167" author="fmatte" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2016 09:57:32 -0700"  >As rightly pointed out, + has more precedence then &amp;gt;&amp;gt;, here is a small program with output&lt;br/&gt;
class Test {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;public static void main(String args[]) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;int a = 8;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;System.out.println(a + a&amp;gt;&amp;gt;1);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;System.out.println(a + (a&amp;gt;&amp;gt;1));&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
output&lt;br/&gt;
8&lt;br/&gt;
12</comment>
